INSERT INTO `aula` VALUES (1,'Talk about yourself',1,'A','<p><strong>Greeting/Introducing yourself</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Greet the student in English. Speak in a natural tone and be careful not to be too fast.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Hi, ___________, my name is __________. </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I am your English teacher today. </em>Or <em>I will be your English teacher today.</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Can you hear me well?</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not interact with you in this moment, use portuguese immediately after the greeting. With basic students, we can use either English or Portuguese. Our priority is to use English, but we have no intention to intimidate students. Be careful with that!</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Good, let&rsquo;s start?</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>What&#39;s your name?!</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Your age?! (idade)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Your location?! (onde mora)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Your marital status (casado? solteiro?)</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n','<p>In this call the student will talk about himself/herself:<br />\r\nGive personal information.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Greeting/Introducing yourself</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Greet the student in English. Speak in a natural tone and be careful not to be too fast.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Hi, ___________, my name is __________. </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I am your English teacher today. </em>Or <em>I will be your English teacher today.</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Can you hear me well?</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not interact with you in this moment, use portuguese immediately after the greeting. With basic students, we can use either English or Portuguese. Our priority is to use English, but we have no intention to intimidate students. Be careful with that!</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Good, let&rsquo;s start?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Let&rsquo;s talk about yourself? </em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Model sentences</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>From now on, you will model sentences: ask-listen and/or model-ask-listen.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>What&rsquo;s your full name? </em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not interact with you in this moment, rephrase the question.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>What&rsquo;s your complete name? </em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not interact with you in this moment, model the answer and immediately ask the question.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>My name is Simone Telles Martins Ramos</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>What&rsquo;s your name?</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>After the student replies, continue the dialogue.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>(student&rsquo;s name), I am 40 years old. </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>How old are you?</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not interact with you in this moment, rephrase the question or use portuguese.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After the student reply, correct pronunciation if necessary. Then, continue the dialogue.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>(student&rsquo;s name), I live in S&atilde;o Paulo?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Where do you live?</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not interact with you in this moment, rephrase the question or use portuguese.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After the student reply, correct pronunciation if necessary. Then, continue the dialogue.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>______, I am married. </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>And you, (student&rsquo;s name)?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Are you married or single?</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not interact with you in this moment, rephrase the question or use portuguese. Explain: married = casado(a), single = solteiro(a), widow/widower = vi&uacute;vo(a).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After the student reply, correct pronunciation if necessary. Then, continue the dialogue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Practice</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>What&rsquo;s your full name? Or What&rsquo;s your complete name? </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>How old are you?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Where do you live?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Are you married or single?</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>during practice the student still has problems to interact with you, model the sentences again. If after modeling, the student continues to present interaction difficulties, you can use portuguese to help or ask the student to try to answer the question using the multimodal material (this is the moment to test its needs and efficiency).</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Production</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now encourage your student to give you his/her personal information.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Now, let&rsquo;s practice more. </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Talk about yourself. </em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>If during production the student still has problems to interact with you, give hints and use verbal cues:</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Your name?!</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Your age?! (idade)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Your location?! (onde mora)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Your marital status (casado? solteiro?)</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>If after the hints, the student continues to present interaction difficulties, it means that he needs more practice and we should encourage student to read the material again and make contact to receive another phone call.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Ending the call</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>(student&rsquo;s name), it is time to finish our class.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Voc&ecirc; atingiu o objetivo de aprendizagem que era &ldquo;talk about yourself&rdquo; , ou seja, fornecer informa&ccedil;&otilde;es pessoais.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Por favor, (re)leia o material interativo e pratique com as atividades do APP. </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Nice talking to you! Foi muito bom conversar com voc&ecirc;.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Thank you, good-bye</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n','<p><a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/export?format=pdf&amp;id=1sVGmPcLqKGKUafigPZ_ucDYjk6xD2M6BWsOYsKYJw6Q\">Download Atividade</a></p>\r\n','','1','2017-05-15 20:07:18','2017-05-22 19:56:14',1),(2,'Time off',2,'A','<p><strong>Greeting/Introducing yourself</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Greet the student in English. Speak in a natural tone and be careful not to be too fast.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Hi, ___________, my name is __________. </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I am your English teacher today. </em>Or <em>I will be your English teacher today.</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Can you hear me well?</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not interact with you in this moment, use portuguese immediately after the greeting. With basic students, we can use either English or Portuguese. Our priority is to use English, but we have no intention to intimidate students. Be careful with that!</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Good, let&rsquo;s start?</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>What&#39;s your favorite hobbie?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Tell me one thing you love doing.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Tell me one place you like to go.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Tell me the frequency you visit this place.</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n','<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Let&rsquo;s talk about your free time, hobbies and places you go. </em>(you can translate uncommon words. Places = lugares, you go = voc&ecirc; vai. Then you repeat the sentence = the places you go)</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Model sentences</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>From now on, you will model sentences: ask-listen and/or model-ask-listen.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Talking about your hobbies</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Let&rsquo;s talk about hobbies!</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I like books, I like arts, I like cooking </em> (you can translate uncommon words. I like cooking - cooking = cozinhar)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>And you? </em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not interact with you in this moment, rephrase the question.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Tell me a hobbie. What do you like? </em>(like = gostar)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>What do you like? </em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>You can help student translate his likes from portuguese to English.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>In my free time I like reading books. And you?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>In your free time you like &hellip;&hellip;. </em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not interact with you in this moment, mix portuguese with English.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>In your free time, you like &hellip;.. (read, sleep&hellip;.) What do you do like? </em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>After the student reply, continue the dialogue.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>(student&rsquo;s name), you like &hellip;. </em>(say the student preference)<em>. That&#39;s cool! </em>(the objective here is to introduce That&rsquo;s cool)</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Talking about places</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Let&rsquo;s talk about places and the frequency you go places.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I go to bookstores in my free time, and you? </em>(you can substitute bookstores for the place that has a link with what the student like).</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not interact with you in this moment, rephrase the question or use portuguese.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>I my free time, I go to bookstores . And you?</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not interact with you in this moment, rephrase the question or use portuguese.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After the student reply, correct pronunciation if necessary. Then, continue the dialogue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Talking about the frequency you go to places</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now on, you will model sentences.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>I prefer bookstores.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I </em><strong><em>always</em></strong><em> go to bookstores. </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>In a month, I go 4 times to bookstores.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I like art galleries.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I </em><strong><em>usually</em></strong><em> go art galleries.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>In a month, I go 2 times to art galleries.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I </em><strong><em>sometimes</em></strong><em> go museums.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>In a month, I go once (1 time) to museums.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>And you?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Tell me a favorite one place and two places you like</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>After the student reply, use portuguese to help with the translation, correct pronunciation if necessary. Then, continue the dialogue.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>To &hellip;. </em>(say the name of the place the student go. Eg. Club.) <em>How often do you go to &hellip;..? Always, Usually, Sometimes </em> (use portuguese to help).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>That&rsquo;s awesome (really good)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>To &hellip;. </em>(say the name of the place the student go. Eg. Club.) <em>How often do you go to &hellip;..? Always, Usually, Sometimes </em> (use portuguese to help).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>That&rsquo;s Interesting</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>To &hellip;. </em>(say the name of the place the student go. Eg. Club.) <em>How often do you go to &hellip;..? Always, Usually, Sometimes </em> (use portuguese to help).</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Production</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now encourage your student to practice with more autonomy</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Now, let&rsquo;s practice more. </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Talk about yourself. </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Now tell me about your favorite hobbie.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Tell me one thing you love doing.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Tell me one place you like to go.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Tell me the frequency you visit this place.</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>If during production the student still has problems to interact with you, give hints and use verbal cues:</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Favorite Hobbie?!</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Love doing?! (ama fazer)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Like doing?! (ama fazer)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>One place?! (um lugar)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Frequency (quantas vezes? Always = sempre; usually = quase sempre; sometimes = as vezes)</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>If after the hints, the student continues to present interaction difficulties, it means that he needs more practice and we should encourage student to read the material again and make contact to receive another phone call.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Ending the call</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>(student&rsquo;s name), it is time to finish our class.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Voc&ecirc; atingiu o objetivo de aprendizagem que era &ldquo;talk about how you spend your time off (your free time)&rdquo; , ou seja, fornecer informa&ccedil;&otilde;es pessoais.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Por favor, (re)leia o material interativo e pratique com as atividades do APP. </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Nice talking to you! Foi muito bom conversar com voc&ecirc;.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Thank you, good-bye</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>After the call</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>After the call, please access student&rsquo;s diary to report its learning progress.</p>\r\n','<p><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/uc?export=download&id=0BzW4ZkRLX_WeOVNHWWdpYkM5Vm8\">Download Atividade</a></p>\r\n','<blockquote>\r\n<p>Gostou da nossa aula? Did you like our class?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>N&oacute;s gostar&iacute;amos de saber o que faz no seu tempo livre.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What do you do in your free time?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Que tal falarmos um pouco sobre seus hobbies, lugares favoritos?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Te espero na pr&oacute;xima liga&ccedil;&atilde;o!</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n','1','2017-05-15 20:07:18','2017-05-23 06:30:30',1),(3,'What is your major?',3,'A','<p><strong>Greeting/Introducing yourself</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Greet the student in English. Speak in a natural tone and be careful not to be too fast.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Hi, ___________, my name is __________. </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I am your English teacher today. </em>Or <em>I will be your English teacher today.</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Can you hear me well?</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not interact with you in this moment, use portuguese immediately after the greeting. With basic students, we can use either English or Portuguese. Our priority is to use English, but we have no intention to intimidate students. Be careful with that!</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Good, let&rsquo;s start?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Talk about your education. </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Now tell me about your major.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Tell me about courses you took.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Tell me about your post graduation.</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n','<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Let&rsquo;s talk about your educational background, places where you studied. </em>(you can translate uncommon words. Places = lugares, you studied = voc&ecirc; estudou. Then you repeat the sentence = places you studied)</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Presentation and Practice</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In this lesson practice and presentation will be done simultaneously due to the complexity of expressing abstract concepts.</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>during practice the student still has problems to interact with you, model the sentences again. If after modeling, the student continues to present interaction difficulties, you can use portuguese to help or ask the student to try to answer the question using the multimodal material (this is the moment to test its needs and efficiency).</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Model sentences</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>From now on, you will model sentences: ask-listen and/or model-ask-listen.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Let&rsquo;s talk about your </em><a href=\"http://www.linguee.com.br/portugues-ingles/search?source=ingles&amp;query=educational+background\"><em>educational background</em></a><em>!</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sentence 1: studied at</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>I studied at Fatec. </em>(you can translate uncommon words. Studied = estudei)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>And you? </em>Motivate the student to say complete sentence.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Fatec </em>(ah! You studied at Fatec. Good!)</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sentence 2: took course</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>I took English Courses. </em>(you can translate uncommon words. Took = fiz)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>And you? </em>Motivate the student to say complete sentence.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not interact with you in this moment, mix portuguese with English. Give examples in English first.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Computing? English? Kumon? Speaking in Public? Presentations?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Course? What course? </em>(Motivate the student to say the course type, you can help with the translation)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Good! You took &hellip;&hellip;</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sentence 3: graduated from</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>I graduated from USP. </em>(you can translate uncommon words. Graduated = graduei )</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>And you? </em>(Motivate the student to say complete sentence.)</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not interact with you in this moment, mix portuguese with English. Give examples in English first.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>UNICAMP? PUC? </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I graduated from FMU.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Great!</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sentence 4: majored in</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>I majored in Engineering. </em>(you can translate uncommon words. Engineering = Engenharia)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>And you? </em>(Motivate the student to say complete sentence.)</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not interact with you in this moment, mix portuguese with English. Give examples in English first.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Mathematics? Science? Biology?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Area? What study area? </em>(Motivate the student to say the course area, you can help with the translation)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Good! You majored in &hellip;.. </em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sentence 5: I am a(n) &hellip;..</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>I am an Engineer. </em>(you can translate uncommon words. Engineer = Engenheiro)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>And you? </em>(Motivate the student to say complete sentence.)</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not interact with you in this moment, mix portuguese with English. Give examples in English first.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>You majored in </em>(say the student&#39;s major) <em>You are &hellip;..</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Talking about your </strong><a href=\"http://www.linguee.com.br/portugues-ingles/search?source=ingles&amp;query=educational+background\"><strong>educational background</strong></a><strong> - answering </strong> <strong>questions</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Now let&rsquo;s suppose you are in a job interview </em>(entrevista de emprego). <em>I am the interviewer </em>(entrevistador)<em> and you are the interviewee </em>(entrevistado). <em>Let&rsquo;s start?</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Question 1: Where did you study? </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Where did you study? </em>(you can translate uncommon words. Where = onde; study = estudou)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I studied at &hellip;. </em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not give you complete answer because of vocabulary, help him.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>At &hellip;. </em>(here you give him the example he mentioned before)</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>Now motivate the student to repeat the sentence</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Now let&rsquo;s repeat: I studied at &hellip;. </em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Question 2: What courses did you take?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>What courses did you take? </em>(you can translate uncommon words. What = quais; take = fez)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I took &hellip;.. </em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not give you complete answer because of vocabulary, help him.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>English &hellip;. </em>(here you give him the example he mentioned before)</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>Now motivate the student to repeat the sentence</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Now let&rsquo;s repeat: I took &hellip;.. </em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Question 3: Where did you graduate?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Where did you graduate? </em>(you can translate uncommon words. Where = onde; graduate = graduou)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I graduated from&hellip;.. </em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not give you complete answer because of vocabulary, help him.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>USP &hellip;. </em>(here you give him the example he mentioned before)</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>Now motivate the student to repeat the sentence</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Now let&rsquo;s repeat: I graduated from&hellip;.. </em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Question 4: What is your major?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>What is your major? </em>(you can translate uncommon words. Major = area de estudo)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I majored in &hellip;.. </em>(Motivate the student to say complete sentence.)</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not interact with you in this moment, mix portuguese with English. Give examples in English first.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Mathematics... </em>(here you give him the example he mentioned before)</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>Now motivate the student to repeat the sentence</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Now let&rsquo;s repeat: I majored in....</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sentence 5: What&rsquo;s your profession?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>What is your profession? </em>(you can translate uncommon words. What = qual; profession = profiss&atilde;o)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I am &hellip;.. </em>(Motivate the student to say complete sentence.)</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not interact with you in this moment, mix portuguese with English. Give examples in English first.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Mathematician... </em>(here you give him the example he mentioned before)</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>Now motivate the student to repeat the sentence</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Now let&rsquo;s repeat: I am a/an&hellip;.</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Talking about majors and professions</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now on, you will model sentences.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>I </em><strong><em>studied at</em></strong><em> Poli.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I </em><strong><em>majored in</em></strong><em> Civil Engineering. </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I </em><strong><em>am</em></strong><em> an Engineer.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I </em><strong><em>graduated from</em></strong><em> USP.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I </em><strong><em>studied at</em></strong><em> ECA.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I </em><strong><em>majored in</em></strong><em> Arts. </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I </em><strong><em>am</em></strong><em> an Artist.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I </em><strong><em>graduated from</em></strong><em> USP.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I </em><strong><em>studied at </em></strong><em>FFLCH.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I </em><strong><em>majored in</em></strong><em> Modern Languages. </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I </em><strong><em>took</em></strong><em> pronunciation courses.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I </em><strong><em>am</em></strong><em> a Teacher.</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Production</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now encourage your student to practice with more autonomy</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>Now, let&rsquo;s practice more. </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Talk about your education. </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Now tell me about your major.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Tell me about courses you took.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Tell me about your post graduation.</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>If after the hints, the student continues to present interaction difficulties, it means that he needs more practice and we should encourage student to read the material again and make contact to receive another phone call.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Ending the call</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><em>(student&rsquo;s name), it is time to finish our class.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Voc&ecirc; atingiu o objetivo de aprendizagem que era &ldquo;talk about your educational background (places you studied)&rdquo; , ou seja, fornecer informa&ccedil;&otilde;es pessoais.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Por favor, (re)leia o material interativo e pratique com as atividades do APP. </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Nice talking to you! Foi muito bom conversar com voc&ecirc;.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Thank you, good-bye</em></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>After the call</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>After the call, please access student&rsquo;s diary to report its learning progress.</p>\r\n','<p><a href=\"https://drive.google.com/uc?export=download&id=0BzW4ZkRLX_WeakJnV1ZyOFRuZE0\">Download Atividade</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n','<blockquote>\r\n<p>Gostou da nossa aula? Did you like our class?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>N&oacute;s gostar&iacute;amos de saber sobre sua educa&ccedil;&atilde;o.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>What are you majored in?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Que tal falarmos um pouco sobre o que e onde voc&ecirc; estudou?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Te espero na pr&oacute;xima liga&ccedil;&atilde;o!</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n','1','2017-05-15 20:07:18','2017-05-23 06:32:34',1),(4,'She is',4,'A','review class 4','this is the content class 4','nice activity','teaser?','1','2017-05-15 20:07:18','2017-05-15 20:07:18',1),(5,'They are',5,'A','review class 5','this is the content class 5','nice activity','teaser?','1','2017-05-15 20:07:18','2017-05-15 20:07:18',1),(6,'They are second class',1,'B','<p>review class 1B</p>\r\n','<p>this is the content class 1B</p>\r\n','nice activity','teaser?','1','2017-05-15 20:07:18','2017-05-22 19:19:23',1),(7,'hullo',1,'A','<p>review class 1</p>\r\n','<p><strong>Interacting with the student</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Greeting/Introducing yourself</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Greet the student in English. Speak in a natural tone and be careful not to be too fast.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Hi, ___________, my name is __________. </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>I am your English teacher today. </em>Or <em>I will be your English teacher today.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><em>Can you hear me well?</em></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not interact with you in this moment, use portuguese immediately after the greeting. With basic students, we can use either English or Portuguese. Our priority is to use English, but we have no intention to intimidate students. Be careful with that!</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Good, let&rsquo;s start?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Let&rsquo;s talk about yourself? </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Model sentences</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>From now on, you will model sentences: ask-listen and/or model-ask-listen.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>What&rsquo;s your full name? </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not interact with you in this moment, rephrase the question.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>What&rsquo;s your complete name? </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not interact with you in this moment, model the answer and immediately ask the question.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>My name is Simone Telles Martins Ramos</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>What&rsquo;s your name?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>After the student replies, continue the dialogue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>(student&rsquo;s name), I am 40 years old. </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>How old are you?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not interact with you in this moment, rephrase the question or use portuguese.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After the student reply, correct pronunciation if necessary. Then, continue the dialogue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>(student&rsquo;s name), I live in S&atilde;o Paulo?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Where do you live?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not interact with you in this moment, rephrase the question or use portuguese.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After the student reply, correct pronunciation if necessary. Then, continue the dialogue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>______, I am married. </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>And you, (student&rsquo;s name)?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Are you married or single?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If the student does not interact with you in this moment, rephrase the question or use portuguese. Explain: married = casado(a), single = solteiro(a), widow/widower = vi&uacute;vo(a).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>After the student reply, correct pronunciation if necessary. Then, continue the dialogue.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Practice</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>What&rsquo;s your full name? Or What&rsquo;s your complete name? </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>How old are you?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Where do you live?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Are you married or single?</em></p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>during practice the student still has problems to interact with you, model the sentences again. If after modeling, the student continues to present interaction difficulties, you can use portuguese to help or ask the student to try to answer the question using the multimodal material (this is the moment to test its needs and efficiency).</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Production</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Now encourage your student to give you his/her personal information.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Now, let&rsquo;s practice more. </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Talk about yourself. </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If during production the student still has problems to interact with you, give hints and use verbal cues:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Your name?!</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Your age?! (idade)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Your location?! (onde mora)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Your marital status (casado? solteiro?)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>If after the hints, the student continues to present interaction difficulties, it means that he needs more practice and we should encourage student to read the material again and make contact to receive another phone call.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Ending the call</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>(student&rsquo;s name), it is time to finish our class.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Voc&ecirc; atingiu o objetivo de aprendizagem que era &ldquo;talk about yourself&rdquo; , ou seja, fornecer informa&ccedil;&otilde;es pessoais.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Por favor, (re)leia o material interativo e pratique com as atividades do APP. </em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Nice talking to you! Foi muito bom conversar com voc&ecirc;.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Thank you, good-bye</em></p>\r\n','nice activity','teaser?','1','2017-05-15 20:07:18','2017-05-17 15:33:12',2),(8,'Aula 2 modulo 2',2,'A','<p>revisao&nbsp;aula 2 modulo 2</p>\r\n','<p>Conteudo aula 2 modulo 2</p>\r\n','<p>atividade aula 2 modulo 2</p>\r\n','<p>TEaser&nbsp;aula 2 modulo 2</p>\r\n','1','2017-05-17 17:04:03','2017-05-17 17:04:03',2);

